On Mon, 25 Apr 2005, Chris M. wrote:

> Would "major heat" (tm?) alter any treating of the control arm? In other words could that be bad?

Probably not, as the spindle is cast.  However, it is possible to overdo
anything.  I wouldn't heat it to glowing!  A lot of people have done this
(or had it done by mechanics) and I haven't heard of any failures

